## Farzana's Verdict

The honest answer in 2026: **there is no longer a real choice to make.** Signet has officially announced JamesAllen.com will shut in early August 2026. The brand becomes a collection inside Blue Nile. The decision was driven by hard numbers — JA sales down 33% to $142.5M last year, a $13M impairment charge on the trade name, and a parent company that concluded the site wasn't worth running independently anymore.

Blue Nile is where you shop. Full stop.

If you're reading this trying to decide: go to Blue Nile, filter for GIA Excellent, G-H color, VS1-VS2 clarity, and check the James Allen section for ring settings. Everything James Allen offered is there — or will be shortly.

